ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Administration Setting
Notes: 1= Paper form, in-lab visit ; 2= Paper form, off-site visit ; 3= Paper form, sent home ; 4= Online survey, in-lab visit ; 5= Online survey, off-site visit ; 6= Online survey, sent home

ElementDescription: The most important part of having a conversation is to:
Notes: 1 = Trade information  ; 0 = Make sure the other person is laughing and smiling

ElementDescription: The goal of a conversation is to:
Notes: 0 = Make the other person like you ; 1 = Find common interests

ElementDescription: One of the rules for having a two-way conversation is:
Notes: 0 = To be an interviewer  ; 1 = Do not be an interviewer

ElementDescription: When you are FIRST getting to know someone, it is important to be:
Notes: 0 = Funny and silly  ; 1 = Serious

ElementDescription: When you are calling a friend on the telephone, it is important to:
Notes: 0 = Tell them your first and last name and where you go to school ; 1 = Have a cover story for calling

ElementDescription: When you are calling a friend on the telephone, you should:
Notes: 1 = Avoid cold calling ; 0 = Let them do most of the talking

ElementDescription: It's a good idea to try to make friends with:
Notes: 0 = Someone who is more popular than you ; 1 = Someone who likes the same things as you

ElementDescription: It's a good idea to have a peer group because:
Notes: 0 = More people will know who you are ; 1 = It protects you from bullying

ElementDescription: When you are trying to join a conversation, the FIRST thing you should do is:
Notes: 1 = Watch to observe the conversation  ; 0 = Make a comment about what they are saying

ElementDescription: When joining a conversation, you should wait for:
Notes: 0 = Someone to invite you to talk  ; 1 = A pause in the conversation

ElementDescription: If you try to join a conversation and the people ignore you:
Notes: 1 = Move on ; 0 = Speak louder and make sure they can hear you

ElementDescription: If you try to join ten different conversations, on average how many times out of ten are you likely to be rejected:
Notes: 0 = 7 out of 10  ; 1 = 5 out of 10

ElementDescription: When having a friend over for a get-together at your home:
Notes: 0 = You should figure out what you are going to do  ; 1 = Have your friend choose the activity

ElementDescription: If you are having a friend over for a get-together and someone else unexpectedly calls that you really like, you should:
Notes: 1 = Invite your other friend over  ; 0 = Tell them that you are busy and will call them later

ElementDescription: Teens like to play sports with other teens who:
Notes: 0 = Score points and play well  ; 1 = Praise them

ElementDescription: When people are not playing by the rules, you should:
Notes: 0 = Nicely remind them what the rules are  ; 1 = Do not referee them

ElementDescription: If another kid teases you or calls you a name, you should:
Notes: 1 = Tease the tease  ; 0 = Tell an adult

ElementDescription: When someone teases you, the best thing to do is:
Notes: 0 = Walk away ; 1 = Make fun of what they said

ElementDescription: If someone is bullying you, the FIRST thing you should do is:
Notes: 0 = Get help from an adult  ; 1 = Avoid the bully

ElementDescription: If you are trying to change your bad reputation, you should:
Notes: 1 = Lay low for a while  ; 0 = Make sure that people get to know you better

ElementDescription: The FIRST thing you should do when you get into an argument with a friend is:
Notes: 1 = Listen and keep your cool ; 0 = Explain your side

ElementDescription: When a friend accuses you of doing something you did not do:
Notes: 1 = Say you are sorry that this happened  ; 0 = Explain your side until they believe you

ElementDescription: TASSK Total Score
total number of missing items
Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
